CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 26, 1953, pg. 1, reads: "SCHENLEY 'INSPIRATIONS' - Schenley High gridders will have oodles of beauty to inspire them in their gridiron battles this season. In addition to these beauties who act as cheerleaders at the games, the school has a majorette corps.  Putting their all into a call to 'fight for dear old Schenley' are...bottom row, left to right, are: Alberta Thompson, Pat Eccard, Barbara Flood, and Barbara Robinson. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Five Schenley High School cheerleaders, left to right: Alberta Thompson, Barbara Robinson (Utterback), unknown woman, Pat Eccard, and Barbara Flood, kneeling in a row outside of Schenley High School
